92
00:08:07,799 --> 00:08:09,900
Oh... In the garden.

93
00:08:10,017 --> 00:08:13,179
- What about Harold and bees?
- I'm allergic to bees.

94
00:08:13,291 --> 00:08:14,689
We'll spray you.

95
00:08:14,806 --> 00:08:19,416
Cold salmon, a lovely
cucumber salad, strawberries.

96
00:08:19,534 --> 00:08:22,885
I'm afraid I am allergic
to strawberries.

97
00:08:24,764 --> 00:08:27,295
Is this all right with you Walter?

98
00:08:28,084 --> 00:08:30,521
Today, I'm consider myself the luckiest...

99
00:08:30,546 --> 00:08:33,927
man-man-man on the face
of the earth-earth-earth.

100
00:08:34,517 --> 00:08:35,977
The Lou Gehrig line from...

101
00:08:36,258 --> 00:08:39,922
Remember, Dad, the Lou
Gehrig line from, uh...

102
00:08:39,992 --> 00:08:41,847
- Pride of the Yankees.
- Pride of the Yankees.

103
00:08:41,872 --> 00:08:43,489
<i>Pride of the Yankees!
Yeah. Yeah.</i>

104
00:08:43,514 --> 00:08:46,224
Baseball. It's baseball.
Historical reference.

105
00:08:46,293 --> 00:08:47,779
I would like to propose a toast.

106
00:08:47,804 --> 00:08:50,848
- Hear, hear.
- To my kid sister.

107
00:08:50,949 --> 00:08:53,191
To Walter and my baby.

108
00:08:53,324 --> 00:08:56,003
To Walter and Annie.

109
00:08:58,008 --> 00:09:01,847
Everyone, please eat
before it gets cold.

110
00:09:04,643 --> 00:09:08,752
Here it is. The Historical
Society wanted this

111
00:09:08,853 --> 00:09:10,447
