give it to them.

112
00:09:10,547 --> 00:09:12,572
Oh, Mum...

113
00:09:12,671 --> 00:09:15,400
I noticed these things
are back in fashion.

114
00:09:15,710 --> 00:09:17,832
Grandmother's dress.

115
00:09:18,012 --> 00:09:22,129
Oh, honey.
He's a lovely man, Annie.

116
00:09:22,236 --> 00:09:24,964
I know he is wonderful,
isn't he?

117
00:09:25,937 --> 00:09:29,082
- And he's such a wonderful athlete.
- Are his folks nice?

118
00:09:29,146 --> 00:09:29,988
You'll love them.

119
00:09:30,013 --> 00:09:32,808
We're going down to DC tonight to
be with them Christmas morning.

120
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:36,404
- How did it happen?
- Well, it's silly, really.

121
00:09:37,006 --> 00:09:40,317
I mean, I'd seen him at the office.
Obviously I'd seen him.

122
00:09:40,342 --> 00:09:41,833
He's the associate publisher.

123
00:09:42,075 --> 00:09:45,955
And then one day, we both ordered
sandwiches from the same place...

124
00:09:45,980 --> 00:09:50,506
and he got my lettuce and tomato on whole
wheat, which, of course, he was allergic to.

125
00:09:50,531 --> 00:09:52,711
And I got his lettuce
and tomato on white.

126
00:09:52,765 --> 00:09:55,045
- How amazing.
- It is, isn't it?

127
00:09:55,176 --> 00:09:57,410
You make a million decisions
that mean nothing

128
00:09:57,435 --> 00:10:00,200
